# GitHub Collaboration Experiment

## Aim

To demonstrate collaboration using GitHub by:

* Forking a repository
* Cloning it locally
* Creating a new branch
* Making changes
* Raising a pull request
* Resolving merge conflicts

## Description

GitHub is a platform that uses Git to help multiple users collaborate on projects.
In this process:

* A repository is forked and cloned
* Changes are made in a new branch
* Updates are submitted through a pull request
* Merge conflicts are resolved before merging

This ensures smooth and organized teamwork.

## Algorithm

1. Open GitHub and select a repository
2. Fork the repository to your account
3. Clone the repository to your local system
4. Create a new branch
5. Make necessary changes in the files
6. Commit the changes
7. Push the changes to GitHub
8. Create a Pull Request
9. Review and resolve merge conflicts (if any)
10. Merge the changes into the main branch

## Result

Successfully demonstrated collaboration using GitHub.


